					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6697939#post-3891758</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6697939/your-guard#post-3891758</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 30 Jul 2018 22:21:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MrBazzle</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3207272</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Ooooooooh. Sweet! I never expected anyone to care enough to make a tale out of any of scips, so for that thank you. Otherwise, I like the nice little twist this gives on the nature of my anomaly.</p> <p>However, this:</p> <blockquote> <p>I think I could tell you why SCP-3845 kept hanging around the kids, now.</p> </blockquote> <p>I'm fond of the idea that a 3845 instance was spoiled and isolated to the point where it ate someone. But I don't like that this person is suggesting that the initial SCP-3845 is a child-eater based off the actions of a separate instance, especially if it contradicts how SCP-3845 acts in the main article. Assuming the narrator knows that 3845 likes to play with children because he read the main article, I don't understand why they would say this.</p> <p>Tentative upvote, though. As well as a crosslink to your tale from my article!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
